st by John Lee Dumas, focused around inspiring entrepreneurs and small biz owners through interviews. Learn from the triumphs and tribulations of fellow self-starters.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Average Episode Length:<\/strong> 30 minutes<\/p>\n<p><strong>Updated:<\/strong> Every Day<\/p>\n<p>See it on <a href=\"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/podcast\/entrepreneur-on-fire-john\/id564001633\">iTunes<\/a> or <a href=\"http:\/\/www.stitcher.com\/podcast\/entrepreneur-on-fire-tim-ferriss-other-incredible-entrepreneurs\">Stitcher<\/a><\/p>\n<h2><strong>11. Build Your Tribe<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>Build Your Tribe is a internet marketing podcast by Chalene Johnson, centered around the community aspect of marketing. Johnson discusses strategies for building and maintaining powerful virtual communities through email marketing, social media, and more.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Average Episode Length:<\/strong> 20 &#8211; 30 minutes<\/p>\n<p><strong>Updated:<\/strong> Every few days<\/p>\n<p>See it on <a href=\"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/podcast\/build-your-tribe-creating\/id910990031\">iTunes<\/a> or <a href=\"http:\/\/www.stitcher.com\/podcast\/chalene-johnson-2\/build-your-tribe-creating-community-email-list-building\">Stitcher<\/a><\/p>\n<h2><strong>12. Online Marketing Made Easy<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p>In this podcast, Amy Porterfield, entrepreneur and co-author of <em>Facebook Marketing All in One for Dummies<\/em>, explains to listeners the best tips and tricks for monetizing your blog online.\u00a0Amy covers a vast array of topics, from video marketing and webinars to Facebook and Twitter; it\u2019s all here.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Average Episode Length:<\/strong> 30 \u2013 60 minutes<\/p>\n<p><strong>Updated:<\/strong> Weekly<\/p>\n<p>Find it on <a href=\"https:\/\/itunes.apple.com\/us\/podcast\/online-marketing-made-easy\/id594703545\">iTunes<\/a> or <a href=\"http:\/\/www.stitcher.com\/podcast\/amy-porterfield\/online-marketing-made-easy-with-amy-porterfield\">Stitcher<\/a><\/p>\n<h2><stro